<p>Of course, our system of government was meant to force compromise, but we have elected such a collection of extremists that it is not possible today, at least not likely. For example, it used to require 3/5 of the Senate to approve a Supreme Court nominee; that’s 60 votes. But in 2017, with a Republican majority, Senate Leader Mitch McConnell overturned the rules so a simple majority – 51 – could stop the debate and call for a vote. That was to get Neil Gorsuch on the court. This was the same nuclear option (actually a parliamentary procedure loophole) Democratic Majority Leader Harry Reid took for the lower courts in 2013, meaning now all nominees for court appointments are approved with a simple majority, that means along partisan lines. The partisan politics that Flake said was ruining government is baked into the rules of government, so a bit of hypocrisy there on all sides.</p>";
    }

